      p These are components of a typographical, static nature.
      section#c-Subhead
        h2 The #[code .c-Subhead] Component
        p.
          Put a #[code .c-Subhead] sibling adjacent to a heading to create
          a subheading for a page. This can be thought of as a
          #[i tagline] or #[i subtitle] for the top-level heading.
        figure
          h1 This is a Page Title
          p.c-Subhead This is a subtitle.
      section#c-FolioTitle
        h2 The #[code .c-FolioTitle] Component
        p.
          On special pages, the top-level header may be a #[code .c-FolioTitle]. To add a little spice,
          use #[code .c-FolioTitle__Cap] on capital letters. The size will make them stand out.
        figure
          h1.c-FolioTitle #[span.c-FolioTitle__Cap T]his is a #[span.c-FolioTitle__Cap s]pecial page title.
      section#c-Lede
