      section#c-ListFootnotes
        h2 The #[code .c-ListFootnotes] Component
        p.
          In the #[code footer] of a document or section, insert a #[code .c-ListFootnotes]
          for a Footnotes List Component.
          Read
          #[a(rel="external" href="https://github.com/chharvey/chharvey.github.io/wiki/Footnotes") my technical report on footnotes]
          for more information.
        figure
          p.
            Conversion gel is made with moon rocks.#[sup: a.Rf#rf-rocks(rel="this" href="#fn-rocks") 1]
            Some panels are made with conversion gel.#[sup: a.Rf#rf-panels(rel="this" href="#fn-panels") 2]
          footer
            ul.c-ListFootnotes
              li.
                #[sup: a.Fn#fn-rocks(rel="this" href="#rf-rocks") 1]
                #[sup: a.Fn#fn-panels(rel="this" href="#rf-panels") 2]
                Don&rsquo;t breathe in moon rocks; they will give you lung cancer.
                This footnote contains a lot of text that goes on and on forever and ever until at some
                point it reaches the next line.
              li.
                #[sup: a.Fn(href="#") 3]
                Another empty footnote. A footnote may include a citation, work cited, or simply a
                parenthetical remark.
